defaultInclusion Scotland (IS) is a national network of disabled peoples' organisations
default and individual disabled people funded by the Scottish Government. Inclusion Scotland’s main aim is to draw attention to the physical, social, economic, cultural and attitudinal barriers that affect disabled people’s everyday lives in Scotland.  
defaultInclusion 
defaultScotland’s membership 
defaultcollectively represents several thousand disabled people from throughout Scotland.  Welfare Reforms
default,
default and in particular changes to Housing Support
default,
default 
defaultcurrently 
defaultco
defaultnstitute the issue of greatest concern to our members.
