defaultScottish Government estimates that 95,000 Scottish households will be affected by the Bedroom Tax in the first year. In Scotland 79% of the households 
defaultexpected to be 
defaultaffected (76,000) contain a disabled person
default. They will lose an average of £13 pw in housing benefit. 
default&#xa0;
default2.2
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultAlthough tenants are being penalised for under-occupying, there is a chronic shortage of 1-bedroom properties.  North Lanarkshire Council, the largest social landlord in Scotland, has 33,000 prope
defaultrties but as of July only 26 of those 
defaultproperties 
defaultcurrently available were single bedroom properties.
