defaultIt is also 
defaultvery likely that there will be a significant overlap between these groups of disabled claimants (e.g. ESA and DLA Lower Rate Care recipients) as both groups have large cohorts of people with learning difficulties and/or mental health issues/cognitive impai
defaultrments (e.g. autism spectrum disorder). 
defaultThus 40% of c
defaultlaimants who have already 
defaultlost entitlement to Employment and Support Allowance have learning difficulties
default 
default/mental health issues whilst over 30% of those currently on DLA Lower Rate Care also have these i
defaultmpairments.
